dietary protein effects For over 100 years, researchers have been studying the effects of dietary protein on human health. Proteins are large molecules made up of amino acids. There are 20 amino acids that our bodies need to function, 12 of which are considered “essential” because our bodies cannot make them. The Recommended Dietary Allowance (RDA) for protein is 0.8 grams per kilogram of body weight. For an average 150-pound adult, this is 56 grams of protein per day. What did the Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions do? The treaty, negotiated by President Ronald Reagan and Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev, eliminated all nuclear and conventional missiles, as well as their launchers, with ranges of 300 to 3,400 miles. The treaty was a breakthrough in arms control, with both sides agreeing to reduce their arsenals by more than 50 percent. The treaty required on-site inspections and the destruction of missiles and launchers. By 1991, 2,692 missiles had been destroyed.
